 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
	   This part of ISO 10303 specifies integrated generic resources for the definition of states and 
	   predicted and observed states. The state definitions and states may be of products, activities, 
	   documents, and other elements defined within ISO 10303.
   </p>
   <p>
	   A state is characterised by a criterium which can be applied to the item. If the criterium is satisfied, 
	   the item is said to be in the given state. The state definition identifies a state and provides the criterium. 
	   When some item is in a state or predicted to be in a state, it is appropriate to record that fact. 
	   This is achieved by the state_observed entity.
   </p>
 </purpose>

